704024f-a.title: Brooklyn: Dock Street - Front Street
704024f-a.text:
Dock Street (left) north from Front Street. In the back-
grommd is the Hanhattan Bridge extendinc to Fanhattan. Un the
north stde of Water Street betveen Dock and Main Street, is
the d storv warehouse Buildinog oT Arbuckle Bros.
April 4, 1938.
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

704460f-b.title: Brooklyn: Front Street - Dock Street
704460f-b.text:
(1)
29-35 Front Street, north side, between Dock and Garrison Streets.
The frame structure was once the mansion of Joshua Sands.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same. The frame house was built in 1786.
April 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, another view, showing in the center of the view the Sands
house (frame). This is only half of the original structure. To the
left of it is a brick building occupying the site of the demolished
section of the Sands house. That building at present is occupied by the
Italian Mission of Santo Spirito.
August 1928.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
